<task id="015" project="sdap-bff-api-and-performance-enhancement-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>GraphServiceClient singleton pooling</title>
    <tags>bff-api, performance</tags>
    <phase>2.1</phase>
    <estimate>2h</estimate>
    <status>pending</status>
    <parallel-group>Wave-2.1</parallel-group>
    <dependencies>003</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Cache singleton GraphServiceClient for app-only operations instead of recreating credential and auth provider on every call.</goal>
    <context>Currently, GraphClientFactory recreates the ClientSecretCredential, TokenCredentialAuthProvider, and GraphServiceClient on every app-only call. This is unnecessary overhead since app-only credentials are long-lived. By caching a singleton GraphServiceClient for app-only operations, we eliminate repeated object creation. OBO (on-behalf-of / delegated) clients must remain per-request since they carry user-specific tokens.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Follow ADR-007: SpeFileStore facade — changes must not leak Graph SDK types
      - App-only GraphServiceClient should be singleton (thread-safe, reusable)
      - OBO (delegated) clients MUST remain per-request (user-specific tokens)
      - Do not change the public API of GraphClientFactory or SpeFileStore
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file path=".claude/adr/ADR-007-spe-file-store.md" reason="SpeFileStore facade and Graph client usage" />
      <file path=".claude/patterns/api/service-registration.md" reason="Service registration and lifetime patterns" />
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read GraphClientFactory.cs — identify the app-only client recreation pattern</step>
    <step id="2">Implement singleton caching for app-only GraphServiceClient (lazy initialization, thread-safe)</step>
    <step id="3">Ensure OBO (delegated) clients remain per-request with user-specific tokens</step>
    <step id="4">Add unit test verifying singleton reuse for app-only client (same instance returned)</step>
    <step id="5">Run dotnet build — verify compilation</step>
    <step id="6">Run dotnet test — verify all tests pass</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <artifact>Updated GraphClientFactory with singleton app-only client</artifact>
    <artifact>Unit test verifying singleton reuse</artifact>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>App-only GraphServiceClient is created once and reused (singleton)</criterion>
    <criterion>OBO (delegated) clients remain per-request</criterion>
    <criterion>Thread-safe initialization (Lazy or similar pattern)</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit test verifies same instance returned for app-only calls</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet build succeeds</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet test passes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
